t to make a difference, the volume is deliberately aimed at a broad audience, including legislators and policymakers, journalists, civil liberties groups, educators, and, above all, the reading public.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aElectronic surveillancezCanada. 0aPrivacy, Right ofzCanada. 0aSocial controlzCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh  aThe New Transparency Project.  abig brother.  agovernment regulation.  aprivacy.  atelecommunications.1 aBennett, Colin J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHaggerty, Kevin D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLyon, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSteeves, Valerie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356784/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles